column2: We had a personal visit- partly cloudy
Thin algae dispersed in water- clear and sunny day.
Clear- sunny- and the water is calm.
Windy and cool- rain a couple of days this week
Rained for 2 days prior to reading- pt. sunny
Above average weed growth in 12 ft. depth- assumed 12:00 time unknown
Long- stringy weeds floating into shore
Partially cloudy- "Eurasian milfoil" identified by the Department of Natural Resources.  There is weed growth in the bay.
Clear- sunny day- water temp is 70 degrees.
Water temp is 72 degrees @ 6".  Eurasian milfoil alert on the lake.
Water temp is 68 degrees @ 1 Ft depth- clear and calm.
Water temp is 68 degrees- partly cloudy.
Took a reading of 29' but not in normal location
Took a reading of 28'9" but not in normal location.
Overcast. light winds. started to rain after reading.
Sunny. warm for this time of year.
Heavy rain night before- overcast- misting.
Sunny- rain a couple hours before.
Sunny. Rained a day or two before.
clear/partly cloudy- had rain 2 days ago. kind of windy now- water still looks cloudy and a little greener than what I am used to- but looks a lot like last observation. Saw a loon a few days ago.
Sunny- water near shore appears very clear- rained yesterday- water cooled some- about 10-15 degrees from last week!
Sunny- water in middle of lake had 5mm size kelly green colored algae flecks. These were not present on shore. Water looked a little cloudy throughout. Rained yesterday- short but hard.
Sunny. First hard frost last night. water looked clear in spots. Looked like starting to turn over in others. Still some green weeds.
Cloudy. Ice came off lake 2 days ago. Lake level very high. Island a canoe paddle blade deep. some milfoil present. South bay as deep as I have ever seen it.

Sunny. Crappies are IN the weeds. weeds are just starting to grow in some areas. most of bottom is void- different from other years- more dead weeds not much standing at all. saw several huge carp from shore. shore temps warming. Dandelions- frogs- leaves on soft wood trees starting to leaf couple of turtles- hostas 3".
Sunny- tree pollen has been in water-milfoil in shallows- green algae on plants- milfoil breaking off and washing up on shore- milfoil thick on North end of lake.
sunny- water warm- clear with particles-doesn't seem as clear as before but still very clear- summer conditions- water very high- lots of rain lately.

partly cloudy- reading taken in partial shade. Water more greenish today. very fine particles. weeds way up and topping. partly cloudy-reading taken in partial shade. Water mre greenish/cloudy- very fine particles. Fishing Very slow. Weeds way up and topping.
very sunny day. water very warm. weeds very tall Very sunny day-warm very calm. Weeds way up. Fishing still slow

very sunny day - cool night last night. water looks a little brown near shore- greener out deep. some plants dying by shore- lilly pads  brown looking very sunny day- cool night last night. water looks a little brown near shore-greener out deep. Some plants dying by shore-lilly pads  Brown looking.

very sunny. milfoil for most part at top of water. Weed survey done last week. fishing slow . many small minnows. water at shore seems a little clearer than last time.  very sunny. Milfoil for most part at top. Weed survey done last week. Fishing slow. Many small minnows- bass. shore water appears a little clearer.
Mostly sunny. Milfoil still standing and a lot of it. Water cold. Beautiful fall. 61 degees today. 1 northern- fishing slow. logging going on.
mostly sunny. milfoil still standing and a lot of it. Water turned over and very cold. Beautiful fall day 61 degrees. fishing very slow.

Mostly sunny. Ice came off yesterday. Water looks a little cloudy. Some bluegills by shore. See fragmentsof green weeds by shoreareas. Water really high. Island 3' under water. Ice off late this year.
Sunny . water cloudy. Few bluegills by North shore.
Sunny. Water cloudy- turnover. Bluegills -northerns and a couple of bass by N. shore. Bass by island. Temp 56-57 by N. shore. 54-55 out deep and by island
Cloudy. Still appears to be in turnover.Some bass by shore- crappies  deeper
Partly sunny. Day of weed treatment. water clearing but still not perfect or usual
After treatment- dat 35. Mostly sunny-calm water a little green w/ very small particles. Fish slow last couple of days
Bright sunny hot day. Long heat wave. Water appears to be clearing a little bit- still brownish- ut maybe a little clearer. No milfoil - but natives!
Bright sunny day. Small bright green algae particles in water and along North shore by Hinca. Water looks a little cloudy. Milfoil present. 15 northerns deep.
Bright sunny day. See milfoil in water and some has come on shore last 3-4 weeks. Water still looks murkier/stained than in past but looks good. Other weed growth healthy.
ice ot yest/ today. water very clear. only weeds standing are sporatic clumps of living milfoil around lake.
7 dat. (grant) some milfoil looks like dying. Some crappies in weeds. Few. found first morel 2 days ago!
water VERY warm. water appears murkey. fishing slow
water dropped 2-3'. some milfoil topping. greenish- brownish tint to water last 4-5 weeks water celery drifting in to shorelines. fishing poor
colors AT peak. water very low. tip of island is almost out. fishing very slow- milfoil topping. water looks murky but better than before.
